sentences.en: In 1949 Bonn was a small, insignificant city.
sentences.cn: 1949年时波恩还是个无足轻重的小城市。

sentences.en: In winter the effect was found to be insignificant.
sentences.cn: 在冬季,这种作用是不明显的.

sentences.en: Miss Tang said, " Mr. Fang, you are too concerned with insignificant details.
sentences.cn: 唐小姐道: “ 方先生真会挑眼!

sentences.en: Phillip saw how insignificant he was.
sentences.cn: 菲利浦看到他是多么不显眼啊!

sentences.en: Some animals may consume insignificant amounts of the primary production.
sentences.cn: 有些动物可以消耗很微量的初级产物.

sentences.en: The amount of material produced during fission is insignificant.
sentences.cn: 裂变时产生的物质数量是不够的.

sentences.en: The Chief Inspector disliked being overburdened with insignificant detail.
sentences.cn: 总督察讨厌在细枝末节上没完没了地纠缠。

sentences.en: The discontinuities they make in the wall are insignificant.
sentences.cn: 测压孔在壁上造成的间断性可以忽略不计.

sentences.en: The effect of type of sizing applicator is insignificant.
sentences.cn: 浸润器的类型的影响不显著.

sentences.en: The levels of chemicals in the river are not insignificant.
sentences.cn: 河水中的化学物质含量不容忽视。

sentences.en: The number of cases is still far from insignificant.
sentences.cn: 病例数仍远不能说已经可以忽略了.

sentences.en: The rate has fallen by an insignificant amount.
sentences.cn: 比率虽有下降,但微不足道.

sentences.en: There was something in the tone of twopence remarkbly insignificant.
sentences.cn: 说起来,两个便士显然是不足挂齿的.

sentences.en: This problem was insignificant compared to others she faced.
sentences.cn: 这一问题与她面临的其他问题比较起来算不得什么.

sentences.en: You realize that your problems are insignificant in comparison.
sentences.cn: 要知道，你的问题相对来说微不足道。

trans.tran_cn: 不重要的，微小的，毫无意义的，不足道
trans.tran_en: too small or unimportant to consider or worry about
